00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:49.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's that old saying,
Michael, knock and the door

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:50.230 align:middle line:90%
will open?

00:10:50.230 --> 00:10:51.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yes.

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:54.270 align:middle line:84%
From the New Testament,
Jesus says knock and the door

00:10:54.270 --> 00:10:55.070 align:middle line:90%
will open.

00:10:55.070 --> 00:10:56.757 align:middle line:84%
Ask and it will
be given unto you.

00:10:56.757 --> 00:10:58.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Much like
what she just said.

00:10:58.340 --> 00:10:59.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Exactly.

00:10:59.270 --> 00:11:01.850 align:middle line:84%
And I love how she
incorporates the angels

00:11:01.850 --> 00:11:04.400 align:middle line:84%
because to paraphrase
John Paul II,

00:11:04.400 --> 00:11:06.740 align:middle line:84%
guardian angels are our
personal patron saint.

00:11:06.740 --> 00:11:08.540 align:middle line:84%
They're not just
there to protect us

00:11:08.540 --> 00:11:09.620 align:middle line:90%
from spiritual danger.

00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:13.460 align:middle line:84%
They can help us in physical
danger, but as a lot of saints,

00:11:13.460 --> 00:11:14.960 align:middle line:84%
Bernard of Clairvaux,
in particular,

00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:16.670 align:middle line:84%
noted, that he often
asked his angel

00:11:16.670 --> 00:11:19.790 align:middle line:84%
to help him with studying,
to help him with virtue,

00:11:19.790 --> 00:11:23.510 align:middle line:84%
to resist temptation because
they're there to protect us,

00:11:23.510 --> 00:11:26.480 align:middle line:84%
but their ultimate goal
is to see us through life

00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:28.340 align:middle line:90%
and the life beyond death.

00:11:28.340 --> 00:11:30.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That little
voice, Michael, we

00:11:30.020 --> 00:11:34.385 align:middle line:84%
all hear in our head, could
that be our guardian angels?

00:11:34.385 --> 00:11:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: It is often
said that our guardian

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:38.420 align:middle line:90%
angels help us and prompt us.

00:11:38.420 --> 00:11:41.090 align:middle line:84%
Most of theologians
and exorcists

00:11:41.090 --> 00:11:43.460 align:middle line:84%
don't believe angels are
able to read our minds.

00:11:43.460 --> 00:11:45.560 align:middle line:84%
But because these
are ancient beings,

00:11:45.560 --> 00:11:49.250 align:middle line:84%
they understand human
intuition and human nature

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:51.448 align:middle line:84%
a lot better than we
do, so it can look

00:11:51.448 --> 00:11:52.740 align:middle line:90%
like they're reading our minds.

00:11:52.740 --> 00:11:55.310 align:middle line:84%
They're not sitting there with
a transcript of what we're

00:11:55.310 --> 00:11:57.540 align:middle line:84%
thinking, but they can
influence our thinking,

00:11:57.540 --> 00:11:59.640 align:middle line:90%
our decision-making.

00:11:59.640 --> 00:12:02.090 align:middle line:84%
Most powerfully, I think
Odile HaumontÃ©, who

00:12:02.090 --> 00:12:05.690 align:middle line:84%
is this wonderful French writer,
wrote "Encounters with Angels."

00:12:05.690 --> 00:12:08.660 align:middle line:84%
She talks about times when
she would be going down

00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:10.940 align:middle line:84%
a dark alley and would
just feel someone tug

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:13.610 align:middle line:84%
at her shoulder or something,
say, hey let's go this way.

00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:13.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Be careful.

00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:14.720 align:middle line:90%
Don't go there.

00:12:14.720 --> 00:12:16.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Exactly.

00:12:16.670 --> 00:12:18.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'm here
today because I

00:12:18.200 --> 00:12:21.080 align:middle line:84%
think I might have been
saved by a guardian angel.

00:12:21.080 --> 00:12:24.920 align:middle line:84%
I am approaching a
four-lane intersection

00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:29.330 align:middle line:84%
and my light is
green, so you go.

00:12:29.330 --> 00:12:31.740 align:middle line:90%
I hear a voice in my head--

00:12:31.740 --> 00:12:33.080 align:middle line:90%
maybe it's the angel--

00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:37.100 align:middle line:84%
and the voice says don't go
through the intersection.

00:12:37.100 --> 00:12:39.140 align:middle line:84%
Don't go through
the intersection.

00:12:39.140 --> 00:12:43.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was so compelling,
I had my green light,

00:12:43.770 --> 00:12:48.660 align:middle line:84%
cars are behind me, and
I stopped right there

00:12:48.660 --> 00:12:50.220 align:middle line:90%
and didn't go through.

00:12:50.220 --> 00:12:53.670 align:middle line:84%
At that moment, Michael,
had I gone through--

00:12:53.670 --> 00:12:56.220 align:middle line:84%
somebody went through
their red light

00:12:56.220 --> 00:12:58.170 align:middle line:84%
and they would
have broadsided me.

00:12:58.170 --> 00:13:00.910 align:middle line:84%
God knows what would
have happened to me.

00:13:00.910 --> 00:13:04.110 align:middle line:84%
But what was that voice that
told me not to go through?

00:13:04.110 --> 00:13:04.960 align:middle line:90%
Was it me?

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:08.902 align:middle line:84%
Am I the intuitive one or is
it an angel tipping me off?

00:13:08.902 --> 00:13:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: I think it could
be a combination of both.

00:13:11.110 --> 00:13:13.470 align:middle line:84%
I think you've been
around a while.

00:13:13.470 --> 00:13:15.970 align:middle line:84%
You definitely learned how to
listen to your inner voice,

00:13:15.970 --> 00:13:18.390 align:middle line:84%
listen to your instincts,
those things that

00:13:18.390 --> 00:13:20.910 align:middle line:84%
have kept the human race alive
for hundreds of thousands

00:13:20.910 --> 00:13:21.840 align:middle line:90%
of years.

00:13:21.840 --> 00:13:25.505 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, there are
supernatural occurrences.

00:13:25.505 --> 00:13:27.380 align:middle line:84%
One of the great things
about guardian angels

00:13:27.380 --> 00:13:28.830 align:middle line:90%
is it shows we're not alone.

00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:32.325 align:middle line:84%
We're not just left
here to exist and die.

00:13:32.325 --> 00:13:33.950 align:middle line:84%
There's something
that watches over us.

00:13:33.950 --> 00:13:36.260 align:middle line:84%
And you, George, have
a reason to live,

00:13:36.260 --> 00:13:38.655 align:middle line:84%
which is why we couldn't lose
you in that intersection.

00:13:38.655 --> 00:13:39.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:13:39.530 --> 00:13:41.000 align:middle line:90%
What's an archangel?

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: An archangel is
one of the higher angels.

00:13:44.330 --> 00:13:48.650 align:middle line:84%
They oversee specifically
God's realm and protect it.

00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:51.050 align:middle line:84%
They are oftentimes-- like
we get guardian angels,

00:13:51.050 --> 00:13:54.840 align:middle line:84%
guardian angels can be
assigned to countries as well.

00:13:54.840 --> 00:13:59.060 align:middle line:84%
For example, at Fatima, one of
the archangels who many believe

00:13:59.060 --> 00:14:02.210 align:middle line:84%
was also Gabriel,
identified himself

00:14:02.210 --> 00:14:04.610 align:middle line:90%
as the angel of Portugal.

00:14:04.610 --> 00:14:07.848 align:middle line:84%
Meaning that he was overseeing
the entire nation of Portugal.

00:14:07.848 --> 00:14:09.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It was his assignment.

00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:11.182 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: It was his
assignment to look over it.

00:14:11.182 --> 00:14:14.900 align:middle line:84%
And so archangels are
almost the commanders,

00:14:14.900 --> 00:14:18.260 align:middle line:84%
if you think of it, over
God's armies on Earth.

00:14:18.260 --> 00:14:21.860 align:middle line:84%
They can also-- they often play
major roles in human affairs,

00:14:21.860 --> 00:14:24.950 align:middle line:84%
most famously, Gregory
the Great Pope of Rome

00:14:24.950 --> 00:14:26.960 align:middle line:90%
in the sixth century.

00:14:26.960 --> 00:14:30.380 align:middle line:84%
A massive plague had moved
through the Mediterranean

00:14:30.380 --> 00:14:32.460 align:middle line:84%
and it was hitting
Rome really hard.

00:14:32.460 --> 00:14:34.580 align:middle line:84%
And so he prayed
and did a procession

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:36.450 align:middle line:90%
to make the plague go away.

00:14:36.450 --> 00:14:39.590 align:middle line:84%
And one day, he and a bunch
of onlookers looked up

00:14:39.590 --> 00:14:42.002 align:middle line:84%
in what's now called
Castel Sant'Angelo--

00:14:42.002 --> 00:14:43.460 align:middle line:84%
and it was called
that because what

00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:45.770 align:middle line:84%
did they see on top
of this ancient castle

00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:48.500 align:middle line:84%
was the Archangel
Michael showing a sword

00:14:48.500 --> 00:14:51.020 align:middle line:84%
and then taking a sword and
putting it back in its sheath,

00:14:51.020 --> 00:14:54.672 align:middle line:84%
signifying to everyone that the
plague was going to be lifted.

00:14:54.672 --> 00:14:56.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We'll talk about
Michael's sword in a moment

00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:58.470 align:middle line:90%
because that's fascinating.

00:14:58.470 --> 00:15:02.390 align:middle line:84%
So the archangels, in the
pecking order of things,

00:15:02.390 --> 00:15:04.018 align:middle line:90%
are a little higher than angels?

00:15:04.018 --> 00:15:05.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yes, they are.

00:15:05.060 --> 00:15:07.460 align:middle line:84%
They're all made with the
same dignity and grace,

00:15:07.460 --> 00:15:10.200 align:middle line:84%
but they have
different assignments.

00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:12.810 align:middle line:84%
As you go further
up, they're closer

00:15:12.810 --> 00:15:15.480 align:middle line:84%
to God's throne, where
you get into the thrones,

00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:18.510 align:middle line:84%
the Dominions, the
Seraphim, and the Cherubim,

00:15:18.510 --> 00:15:20.880 align:middle line:84%
whose entire work
is surrounding God.

00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:22.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they have
more angelic powers

00:15:22.920 --> 00:15:24.930 align:middle line:90%
than regular angels?

00:15:24.930 --> 00:15:26.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: They seem
to have equal powers

00:15:26.790 --> 00:15:28.530 align:middle line:84%
and are made in equal
dignity, but they

00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:31.110 align:middle line:84%
have greater
assignments and also can

00:15:31.110 --> 00:15:32.940 align:middle line:84%
take on a more
terrifying appearance.

00:15:32.940 --> 00:15:37.650 align:middle line:84%
That's where the Old Testament
describes like the Cherubim are

00:15:37.650 --> 00:15:41.100 align:middle line:84%
six-winged, many-eyed,
and terrifying

00:15:41.100 --> 00:15:42.360 align:middle line:90%
looking from description.

00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:44.908 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can an archangel
be a guardian angel?

00:15:44.908 --> 00:15:46.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: They've shown
up in the Old Testament.

00:15:46.950 --> 00:15:49.590 align:middle line:90%
I mentioned Tobit and Raphael.

00:15:49.590 --> 00:15:53.880 align:middle line:84%
Raphael was taking-- he
appeared as a human to Tobit

00:15:53.880 --> 00:15:56.880 align:middle line:84%
and his son, Tobias, and
was just helping them

00:15:56.880 --> 00:16:00.240 align:middle line:84%
through this period where
Tobias was looking for a wife.

00:16:00.240 --> 00:16:02.280 align:middle line:84%
And then only
towards the end, he

00:16:02.280 --> 00:16:05.070 align:middle line:84%
reveals that I'm Rafael,
one of the archangels

00:16:05.070 --> 00:16:06.990 align:middle line:90%
who surrounds God's throne.

00:16:06.990 --> 00:16:09.450 align:middle line:84%
And he was assigned,
in many ways,

00:16:09.450 --> 00:16:11.370 align:middle line:84%
it sounded like a love
story, but he was also

00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:14.580 align:middle line:84%
assigned specifically
to look after Tobit.

00:16:14.580 --> 00:16:16.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me
an archangel story.

00:16:16.300 --> 00:16:18.440 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what is their role?

00:16:18.440 --> 00:16:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Their role-- probably
the most famous when we get

00:16:20.940 --> 00:16:24.390 align:middle line:84%
around to Christmas, we'll hear
the words of the archangel to--

00:16:24.390 --> 00:16:28.140 align:middle line:84%
