00:16:59.220 --> 00:17:01.810 align:middle line:90%
What is a cherubim?

00:17:01.810 --> 00:17:06.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: The cherubim are the
ones who surround God's throne.

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:08.890 align:middle line:84%
And their job is
basically to sing

00:17:08.890 --> 00:17:10.900 align:middle line:90%
the praise and glory of God.

00:17:10.900 --> 00:17:13.150 align:middle line:84%
When they encounter
us, they're usually--

00:17:13.150 --> 00:17:15.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they the little
things we see hovering around?

00:17:15.750 --> 00:17:16.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: No, they are.

00:17:16.750 --> 00:17:18.940 align:middle line:84%
That's how a lot of artists
depict them because--

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:20.232 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Little tiny
wings and all that.

00:17:20.232 --> 00:17:21.032 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yeah.

00:17:21.032 --> 00:17:22.990 align:middle line:84%
Little tiny winged
babies flying around.

00:17:22.990 --> 00:17:24.880 align:middle line:84%
In the Old Testament,
they sound almost

00:17:24.880 --> 00:17:28.349 align:middle line:84%
like ancient
terrors, which is why

00:17:28.349 --> 00:17:30.960 align:middle line:84%
one of my favorite things
about biblical angels

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:33.480 align:middle line:84%
is they always start
with, be not afraid.

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:36.510 align:middle line:90%
Do not fear us.

00:17:36.510 --> 00:17:38.212 align:middle line:84%
Which I remember
reading like, why

00:17:38.212 --> 00:17:40.170 align:middle line:84%
were people so terrified
that when you find out

00:17:40.170 --> 00:17:43.020 align:middle line:84%
the descriptions of angels
and also all that power

00:17:43.020 --> 00:17:45.240 align:middle line:84%
and light that's
suddenly in front of you,

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:48.750 align:middle line:84%
it's easy for humans to
fall into terror of them?

00:17:48.750 --> 00:17:51.870 align:middle line:84%
But that they're-- at least
the ones sent by God are there

00:17:51.870 --> 00:17:52.740 align:middle line:90%
to help us.

00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:55.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do some people
fear angels, Michael?

00:17:55.660 --> 00:17:56.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yes.

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:58.542 align:middle line:84%
And I think a little
fear is healthy.

00:17:58.542 --> 00:18:00.000 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a-- I don't
think I'm going

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.575 align:middle line:84%
to get attacked by
a bear every day,

00:18:01.575 --> 00:18:03.450 align:middle line:84%
but when I see a bear
in the wild, of course,

00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:05.770 align:middle line:84%
I get that internal sense
that's saying, OK, careful.

00:18:05.770 --> 00:18:06.570 align:middle line:90%
That's--

00:18:06.570 --> 00:18:07.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Fight or flight.

00:18:07.590 --> 00:18:07.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yeah.

00:18:07.950 --> 00:18:10.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that has
the power to swipe my head off.

00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:12.240 align:middle line:90%
Angels are far more powerful.

00:18:12.240 --> 00:18:15.180 align:middle line:84%
They have patience,
they have everything

00:18:15.180 --> 00:18:16.690 align:middle line:90%
they need to take us down.

00:18:16.690 --> 00:18:20.050 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of people, when
they encounter angels,

00:18:20.050 --> 00:18:22.570 align:middle line:84%
especially when the angels
appear in their full glory,

00:18:22.570 --> 00:18:24.730 align:middle line:90%
are immediately afraid.

00:18:24.730 --> 00:18:28.090 align:middle line:84%
I recall one patient
who encountered an angel

00:18:28.090 --> 00:18:30.370 align:middle line:84%
while his father
was on his deathbed.

00:18:30.370 --> 00:18:33.430 align:middle line:84%
And when he saw the angelic
being, his father was at peace.

00:18:33.430 --> 00:18:36.070 align:middle line:84%
He himself was
filled with terror

00:18:36.070 --> 00:18:40.220 align:middle line:84%
and he wanted to run from the
room, but also what's going on?

00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:42.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now you said
that Lucifer was an angel.

00:18:42.220 --> 00:18:43.630 align:middle line:90%
Was he an archangel?

00:18:43.630 --> 00:18:44.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: He was an archangel.

00:18:44.950 --> 00:18:47.410 align:middle line:84%
So he was one of
the higher angels.

00:18:47.410 --> 00:18:50.860 align:middle line:84%
The other angels were of
various different powers.

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:54.310 align:middle line:84%
Some think that Beelzebub
might have been a seraph.

00:18:54.310 --> 00:18:57.190 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to tell,
but he was indeed

00:18:57.190 --> 00:18:58.300 align:middle line:90%
one of the highest angels.

00:18:58.300 --> 00:19:00.520 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, his very
name means light.

00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:02.710 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes he's even
called the light bringer

00:19:02.710 --> 00:19:04.540 align:middle line:90%
in the old stories.

00:19:04.540 --> 00:19:06.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you
pray to an angel?

00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:08.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: You can
absolutely pray to an angel.

00:19:08.860 --> 00:19:10.990 align:middle line:84%
Their goal is not so
much to act as gods

00:19:10.990 --> 00:19:14.980 align:middle line:84%
but to act as intermediaries
between God and man,

00:19:14.980 --> 00:19:16.270 align:middle line:90%
or to act as messengers.

00:19:16.270 --> 00:19:18.580 align:middle line:84%
But your guardian
angel is a great person

00:19:18.580 --> 00:19:21.110 align:middle line:90%
to pray to, to say--

00:19:21.110 --> 00:19:23.080 align:middle line:84%
probably for me, what
I've learned from reading

00:19:23.080 --> 00:19:25.455 align:middle line:84%
is that the best thing you
can say to your guardian angel

00:19:25.455 --> 00:19:27.137 align:middle line:90%
is simple gratitude-- thank you.

00:19:27.137 --> 00:19:27.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:31.630 align:middle line:84%
Now on Gaia's Ascension Keepers,
our friend William Henry

00:19:31.630 --> 00:19:35.830 align:middle line:84%
discusses archangels, the
Seraphim, and Cherubim,

00:19:35.830 --> 00:19:37.300 align:middle line:90%
as you've been talking about.

00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:38.100 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:19:38.100 --> 00:19:42.040 align:middle line:10%
>> According to this system, the
Watchers are the highest angels

00:19:42.040 --> 00:19:46.150 align:middle line:10%
possible and were ruled
over by four of their own.

00:19:46.150 --> 00:19:51.610 align:middle line:84%
The great angels known as
Michael, Gabriel, Raphael,

00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:53.890 align:middle line:90%
and Ariel.

00:19:53.890 --> 00:19:57.130 align:middle line:84%
These are among the good
watchers we will discuss,

00:19:57.130 --> 00:20:04.250 align:middle line:84%
as is Metatron, who is actually
the transformed human Enoch.

00:20:04.250 --> 00:20:08.990 align:middle line:84%
The watchers are the mighty
Seraphim, the winged and fiery

00:20:08.990 --> 00:20:11.600 align:middle line:84%
serpents, as they were
known, the burning ones,

00:20:11.600 --> 00:20:15.650 align:middle line:84%
who formerly guarded
the gate to Eden.

00:20:15.650 --> 00:20:18.560 align:middle line:10%
They came from God's
throne, where they

00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:21.680 align:middle line:10%
served on God's divine council.

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:24.470 align:middle line:90%
But they decided to leave.

00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:27.110 align:middle line:84%
They crossed a
forbidden boundary

00:20:27.110 --> 00:20:31.030 align:middle line:90%
and took on earthly bodies.

00:20:31.030 --> 00:20:34.360 align:middle line:84%
In Christian art, the Seraphim
are portrayed as sixed-winged

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:38.590 align:middle line:84%
and covered with
feathers and eyes--

00:20:38.590 --> 00:20:40.990 align:middle line:84%
an appropriate
attribute of those who

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:45.250 align:middle line:90%
watch or guard God's throne.

00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:48.910 align:middle line:84%
Their swirling
bodies are toroidal.

00:20:48.910 --> 00:20:53.410 align:middle line:84%
They are composed of
pure love and pure light.

00:20:53.410 --> 00:20:57.460 align:middle line:84%
In his famous vision, Isaiah
saw the Seraphim enthroned

00:20:57.460 --> 00:20:59.920 align:middle line:84%
above the Ark of the
Covenant in the Holy

00:20:59.920 --> 00:21:03.100 align:middle line:90%
of Holies of Solomon's temple.

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:08.910 align:middle line:84%
They stood above Yahweh as
he sat on his Ark throne.

00:21:08.910 --> 00:21:11.600 align:middle line:84%
They are believed to be the
same as the Cherubim of 1

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:14.210 align:middle line:84%
Chronicles, whose
wings were stretched

00:21:14.210 --> 00:21:15.785 align:middle line:90%
above the Ark of the Covenant.

00:21:15.785 --> 00:21:18.360 align:middle line:90%


00:21:18.360 --> 00:21:21.360 align:middle line:10%
The root of Seraphim comes
either from the Hebrew verb

00:21:21.360 --> 00:21:25.020 align:middle line:10%
seraph, to burn, or the
Hebrew noun, seraph,

00:21:25.020 --> 00:21:28.770 align:middle line:10%
meaning a fiery flying serpent.

00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:29.970 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:21:29.970 --> 00:21:33.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: For so many
different cultures

00:21:33.360 --> 00:21:40.790 align:middle line:84%
have illustrated these angels
and cherubims and seraphins.

00:21:40.790 --> 00:21:43.083 align:middle line:84%
It's got to tell you
something was happening.

00:21:43.083 --> 00:21:44.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Absolutely.

00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:48.220 align:middle line:84%
Especially when you look into
all the Abrahamic faiths that

00:21:48.220 --> 00:21:51.430 align:middle line:84%
came from the desert, they not
only had angels, of course,

00:21:51.430 --> 00:21:54.220 align:middle line:84%
but they also would talk about
demons and other creatures

00:21:54.220 --> 00:21:55.990 align:middle line:90%
of the night.

00:21:55.990 --> 00:21:57.940 align:middle line:84%
In some ways, it
takes the terror

00:21:57.940 --> 00:22:00.790 align:middle line:84%
that we just naturally
feel as humans

00:22:00.790 --> 00:22:05.050 align:middle line:84%
in this big chaotic universe,
and they bring order to it.

00:22:05.050 --> 00:22:10.602 align:middle line:84%
They help us to see beyond just
the eat and live parts of life,

00:22:10.602 --> 00:22:12.310 align:middle line:84%
but to see that there's
something greater

00:22:12.310 --> 00:22:13.990 align:middle line:90%
and bigger than us.

00:22:13.990 --> 00:22:18.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are the angels
still under the realm of God?

00:22:18.150 --> 00:22:19.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: The angels
that stayed with God

00:22:19.900 --> 00:22:22.150 align:middle line:84%
after the rebellion are
still under the realm of God.

00:22:22.150 --> 00:22:24.550 align:middle line:84%
They still operate
under God's will.

00:22:24.550 --> 00:22:28.030 align:middle line:84%
And they still seek
to enact his will.

00:22:28.030 --> 00:22:31.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they the
messengers of deception

00:22:31.840 --> 00:22:36.248 align:middle line:84%
or are they the messengers
of grand things to do?

00:22:36.248 --> 00:22:38.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: They're the
messengers of grand things

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:41.510 align:middle line:84%
even if they don't seem so
grand in our view of things.

00:22:41.510 --> 00:22:44.230 align:middle line:84%
They are the messengers that
help the human race get back

00:22:44.230 --> 00:22:46.760 align:middle line:84%
on the right path, but
there are, of course,

00:22:46.760 --> 00:22:49.300 align:middle line:84%
the fallen angels
who can deceive us.

00:22:49.300 --> 00:22:51.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is the Metatron?

00:22:51.370 --> 00:22:56.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Metatron is the
voice of God incarnate.

00:22:56.530 --> 00:22:58.990 align:middle line:84%
So when God needed to speak
to, say, Adam and Eve,

00:22:58.990 --> 00:23:02.230 align:middle line:84%
it's thought in some mysticism
that he would send Metatron,

00:23:02.230 --> 00:23:05.710 align:middle line:84%
who would act as the voice of
God, whose very voice could

00:23:05.710 --> 00:23:07.760 align:middle line:90%
shatter a person's mind.

00:23:07.760 --> 00:23:10.960 align:middle line:84%
And so there was another
messenger between God and man.

00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:12.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:23:12.980 --> 00:23:14.690 align:middle line:90%
It is fascinating.

00:23:14.690 --> 00:23:15.590 align:middle line:90%
Is it not?

00:23:15.590 --> 00:23:17.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: It's
very fascinating.

00:23:17.060 --> 00:23:20.480 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting because
we know that God--

00:23:20.480 --> 00:23:22.430 align:middle line:84%
in at least my
spiritual tradition,

00:23:22.430 --> 00:23:25.310 align:middle line:84%
we know God uses humans
often to fulfill his will.

00:23:25.310 --> 00:23:27.110 align:middle line:84%
It's so fascinating
to think about.

00:23:27.110 --> 00:23:28.730 align:middle line:84%
There's a realm
beyond and something

00:23:28.730 --> 00:23:31.650 align:middle line:84%
that we can't even comprehend
that's doing exactly what we're

00:23:31.650 --> 00:23:32.450 align:middle line:90%
doing.

00:23:32.450 --> 00:23:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Michael, you talked
about the sword of St. Michael.

00:23:36.260 --> 00:23:37.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yes.

00:23:37.130 --> 00:23:40.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: First of all,
explain St. Michael.

00:23:40.430 --> 00:23:43.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: So Saint Michael
is probably the most famous

00:23:43.380 --> 00:23:44.180 align:middle line:90%
of archangels.

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:46.820 align:middle line:84%
You can tell by my first
name, I really like the guy.

00:23:46.820 --> 00:23:51.500 align:middle line:10%
He is the one that
had casted Lucifer out

00:23:51.500 --> 00:23:53.660 align:middle line:10%
during the rebellion
and actually slew him

00:23:53.660 --> 00:23:57.320 align:middle line:10%
with a sword before casting
them down into the Earth.

00:23:57.320 --> 00:24:01.100 align:middle line:84%
From there, he has been known
to be a protector, a fighter.

00:24:01.100 --> 00:24:04.250 align:middle line:84%
He's the Patron Saint of
soldiers and warriors.

00:24:04.250 --> 00:24:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And he has appeared
throughout human history

00:24:06.650 --> 00:24:08.180 align:middle line:90%
in the strangest of places.

00:24:08.180 --> 00:24:10.850 align:middle line:84%
We mention Rome, to
talk about the plague.

00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:15.735 align:middle line:84%
He's also appeared to
different mystics and people

00:24:15.735 --> 00:24:16.740 align:middle line:90%
who had seen Mary.

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.770 align:middle line:84%
He will often be the
forerunner before people

00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:21.870 align:middle line:84%
will have Marian
visions, basically

00:24:21.870 --> 00:24:26.050 align:middle line:84%
to let people prepare, be
ready for this to happen.

00:24:26.050 --> 00:24:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And so while he's the Warrior
Saint and the archetype

00:24:31.350 --> 00:24:36.060 align:middle line:84%
of a Christian Warrior, he's
also the messenger still.

00:24:36.060 --> 00:24:39.050 align:middle line:84%
So he still fulfills
that angelic function.

00:24:39.050 --> 00:24:42.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There is a piece
that I run during Christmas

00:24:42.870 --> 00:24:46.890 align:middle line:84%
on the radio show, that was
done by a great broadcaster

00:24:46.890 --> 00:24:49.770 align:middle line:84%
by the name of Lee
Allen, and it is

00:24:49.770 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:90%
called "A Letter to Michael."

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:59.370 align:middle line:84%
And it depicts a soldier
writing back to his mother

00:24:59.370 --> 00:25:04.770 align:middle line:84%
about the Korean War and how he
was about ready to get killed,

00:25:04.770 --> 00:25:08.160 align:middle line:84%
when all of a sudden,
out of nowhere,

00:25:08.160 --> 00:25:12.420 align:middle line:84%
Michael appears with his
sword and protects him

00:25:12.420 --> 00:25:14.350 align:middle line:90%
from the enemy.

00:25:14.350 --> 00:25:17.500 align:middle line:84%
It's an amazing
depiction on many things

00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:18.790 align:middle line:90%
you've just illustrated.

00:25:18.790 --> 00:25:19.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yeah.

00:25:19.590 --> 00:25:20.950 align:middle line:90%
And it's interesting.

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:24.040 align:middle line:84%
A couple of soldiers have
had visions of St. Michael.

00:25:24.040 --> 00:25:27.520 align:middle line:84%
One of the most famous, there's
called the Angel of Belgium

00:25:27.520 --> 00:25:29.710 align:middle line:84%
that many soldiers
thought was Michael,

00:25:29.710 --> 00:25:32.080 align:middle line:84%
but it was during
World War I when

00:25:32.080 --> 00:25:36.010 align:middle line:84%
British had to flee Belgium
while the Germans advanced.

00:25:36.010 --> 00:25:38.260 align:middle line:84%
And at this time,
there was a lot

00:25:38.260 --> 00:25:40.660 align:middle line:84%
of crimes against humanity
happening in Belgium.

00:25:40.660 --> 00:25:44.930 align:middle line:84%
We're talking crucifixions,
deep crimes against humanity.

00:25:44.930 --> 00:25:45.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Horrible.

00:25:45.730 --> 00:25:47.688 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: And while the
soldiers were fleeing,

00:25:47.688 --> 00:25:49.930 align:middle line:84%
they weren't sure they
were going to flee in time.

00:25:49.930 --> 00:25:51.890 align:middle line:84%
Thousands-- I'm not
talking about just a couple

00:25:51.890 --> 00:25:53.740 align:middle line:84%
of dozen-- thousands
of soldiers saw

00:25:53.740 --> 00:25:57.390 align:middle line:84%
an angel appear at the German
lines holding back the Germans.

00:25:57.390 --> 00:25:58.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It was Michael.

00:25:58.390 --> 00:25:59.473 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: It was Michael.

00:25:59.473 --> 00:26:02.980 align:middle line:84%
Sword unsheathed, helping
people flee and evacuate.

00:26:02.980 --> 00:26:04.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is Michael
the only angel

00:26:04.570 --> 00:26:06.572 align:middle line:90%
that deals with protection?

00:26:06.572 --> 00:26:08.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: All the angels
deal with protection.

00:26:08.530 --> 00:26:11.050 align:middle line:84%
He seems to have a
particular love of soldiers,

00:26:11.050 --> 00:26:14.260 align:middle line:84%
though, especially the
boots on the ground

00:26:14.260 --> 00:26:16.100 align:middle line:90%
that are in the field.

00:26:16.100 --> 00:26:18.070 align:middle line:84%
A couple other
encounters happened

00:26:18.070 --> 00:26:19.840 align:middle line:84%
in World War I, where
soldiers wrote back

00:26:19.840 --> 00:26:23.080 align:middle line:84%
that they saw Saint Michael
warning them to flee

00:26:23.080 --> 00:26:25.600 align:middle line:84%
or telling them to
get down minutes

00:26:25.600 --> 00:26:27.730 align:middle line:84%
before the bombs
started falling.

00:26:27.730 --> 00:26:31.960 align:middle line:84%
So he takes an interest in the
low-level soldiers, it seems.

00:26:31.960 --> 00:26:34.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There are various areas
around the country that Michael

00:26:34.750 --> 00:26:35.770 align:middle line:90%
has been seen.

00:26:35.770 --> 00:26:39.100 align:middle line:84%
We've got a little
depiction on the spots.

00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:40.232 align:middle line:90%
He's all over the place.

00:26:40.232 --> 00:26:41.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He's
all over the place.

00:26:41.690 --> 00:26:44.260 align:middle line:84%
So this is what's called
the Sword of Saint Michael,

00:26:44.260 --> 00:26:46.150 align:middle line:84%
and it runs in
this straight line.

00:26:46.150 --> 00:26:48.760 align:middle line:84%
This has only been discovered
in the last 100 years

00:26:48.760 --> 00:26:51.820 align:middle line:84%
that people noticed all
these monasteries associated

00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:54.400 align:middle line:84%
with Saint Michael ran
in a straight line.

00:26:54.400 --> 00:26:56.440 align:middle line:84%
And what's even
more fascinating,

00:26:56.440 --> 00:27:01.630 align:middle line:84%
this follows the summer
equinox, so it's actually

00:27:01.630 --> 00:27:03.100 align:middle line:90%
aligning with the stars.

00:27:03.100 --> 00:27:04.450 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Michael is seasonal.

00:27:04.450 --> 00:27:05.830 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:27:05.830 --> 00:27:08.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He at least keeps
an eye on the sky for us.

00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:11.170 align:middle line:84%
And you can see that
right across the two Saint

00:27:11.170 --> 00:27:14.440 align:middle line:84%
Michael's monastery-- one in
Cornwall and one in Normandy--

00:27:14.440 --> 00:27:17.860 align:middle line:84%
those were two-plate
mountain, tidal mountains

00:27:17.860 --> 00:27:20.890 align:middle line:84%
that you can't access them
when the tide is high.

00:27:20.890 --> 00:27:22.840 align:middle line:84%
And Saint Michael
appeared on each spot,

00:27:22.840 --> 00:27:26.020 align:middle line:84%
so of course, they built a
massive monastery to him.

00:27:26.020 --> 00:27:29.680 align:middle line:84%
And as you get further down,
down there in Southern Italy

00:27:29.680 --> 00:27:31.630 align:middle line:84%
is also where Saint
Michael appeared

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:34.000 align:middle line:90%
to a group of soldiers.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:36.910 align:middle line:84%
Right before the
Saracens invaded,

00:27:36.910 --> 00:27:39.670 align:middle line:84%
he basically showed
to the small village,

00:27:39.670 --> 00:27:41.500 align:middle line:84%
warned them they were
about to be invaded

00:27:41.500 --> 00:27:46.970 align:middle line:84%
and to fortify their place,
and they survived the invasion.

00:27:46.970 --> 00:27:51.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Michael, what does
Saint Michael look like?

00:27:51.500 --> 00:27:53.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: That's
a tough question.

00:27:53.090 --> 00:27:56.060 align:middle line:84%
Angels, they don't have
physical bodies like us,

00:27:56.060 --> 00:27:59.480 align:middle line:84%
so they can often appear as
humans however they like.

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:02.480 align:middle line:84%
But in almost all
accounts of him,

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:07.010 align:middle line:84%
he is shown to be a warrior with
a sword, depending on what--

00:28:07.010 --> 00:28:10.063 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is he the only
archangel that is doing that?

00:28:10.063 --> 00:28:11.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He's
the only archangel

00:28:11.480 --> 00:28:14.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm aware of that appears
to humans with a sword

00:28:14.660 --> 00:28:18.500 align:middle line:84%
like as if to make sure
we understand what he is.

00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:22.970 align:middle line:84%
The sword itself, what's
its reasoning behind that?

00:28:22.970 --> 00:28:25.100 align:middle line:84%
The sword is sacred
in a lot of ways

00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:27.890 align:middle line:84%
because it was the weapon
that defeated Satan.

00:28:27.890 --> 00:28:30.140 align:middle line:84%
So, in a lot of
spirituality, we like

00:28:30.140 --> 00:28:33.200 align:middle line:84%
to say that we want to
be cloaked, protected

00:28:33.200 --> 00:28:37.850 align:middle line:84%
by the sword of Saint Michael,
the one that slew demons.

00:28:37.850 --> 00:28:40.950 align:middle line:84%
And by that weapon
itself, it's taken

00:28:40.950 --> 00:28:44.550 align:middle line:84%
on a lot of meaning throughout
Christian mysticism, which

00:28:44.550 --> 00:28:47.340 align:middle line:84%
is why when he announced to
Saint Gregory the plague was

00:28:47.340 --> 00:28:50.040 align:middle line:84%
leaving, he was sheathing the
sword as if God's wrath was

00:28:50.040 --> 00:28:52.860 align:middle line:90%
suddenly going to go away.

00:28:52.860 --> 00:28:56.670 align:middle line:84%
Anytime he's depicted as holding
the sword in his hands, that

00:28:56.670 --> 00:29:00.960 align:middle line:84%
means battle is about to happen,
either spiritual or physical.

00:29:00.960 --> 00:29:04.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do other events
occur when Saint Michael

00:29:04.080 --> 00:29:08.820 align:middle line:84%
has been witnessed, like
natural tragedies or anything

00:29:08.820 --> 00:29:09.620 align:middle line:90%
like that?

00:29:09.620 --> 00:29:09.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yeah.

00:29:09.850 --> 00:29:11.200 align:middle line:90%
I had mentioned a--

00:29:11.200 --> 00:29:13.780 align:middle line:84%
particularly invasions,
but he has often

00:29:13.780 --> 00:29:16.690 align:middle line:84%
appeared to mystics whenever
there's been a plague.

00:29:16.690 --> 00:29:19.150 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if he ever appeared
before COVID or anything

00:29:19.150 --> 00:29:22.390 align:middle line:84%
like that, but in ancient
times, many people

00:29:22.390 --> 00:29:25.270 align:middle line:84%
would see him
warning of a plague,

00:29:25.270 --> 00:29:26.962 align:middle line:84%
warning that this
was going to happen.

00:29:26.962 --> 00:29:28.420 align:middle line:84%
And that's because
in the medieval,

00:29:28.420 --> 00:29:32.075 align:middle line:84%
understanding plagues was part
of God's wrath to correct us.

00:29:32.075 --> 00:29:32.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:29:32.950 --> 00:29:34.750 align:middle line:90%
How about the other archangels?

00:29:34.750 --> 00:29:39.760 align:middle line:84%
Do they have similar traits
as Michael, or is he the one?

00:29:39.760 --> 00:29:42.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He's the most
popular, the most famous.

00:29:42.520 --> 00:29:47.200 align:middle line:84%
You can find authors of St.
Michael just about anywhere.

00:29:47.200 --> 00:29:50.800 align:middle line:84%
He got especially famous
in the 19th century

00:29:50.800 --> 00:29:53.950 align:middle line:84%
when Pope Leo the 13th had
a vision of St. Michael

00:29:53.950 --> 00:29:56.150 align:middle line:90%
and the devil at an argument.

00:29:56.150 --> 00:29:58.210 align:middle line:84%
And that's why he
promoted the Saint Michael

00:29:58.210 --> 00:30:01.437 align:middle line:84%
prayer, which many Catholics
remember praying after mass.

00:30:01.437 --> 00:30:03.520 align:middle line:84%
Saint Michael the Archangel,
protect us in battle,

00:30:03.520 --> 00:30:05.520 align:middle line:84%
be our defense against
the wickedness and snares

00:30:05.520 --> 00:30:08.260 align:middle line:84%
of the devil, and
that was prayed

00:30:08.260 --> 00:30:12.170 align:middle line:84%
by thousands of Catholics
every Sunday for years.

00:30:12.170 --> 00:30:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, we've heard
depictions of Michael.

00:30:14.350 --> 00:30:15.800 align:middle line:90%
I mentioned the one in Korea.

00:30:15.800 --> 00:30:16.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yes.

00:30:16.600 --> 00:30:19.090 align:middle line:90%


00:30:19.090 --> 00:30:22.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are there any
boundaries to this archangel?

00:30:22.100 --> 00:30:24.735 align:middle line:90%
Are there places it will not go?

00:30:24.735 --> 00:30:27.360 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: As far as I'm aware,
they'll go just about anywhere,

00:30:27.360 --> 00:30:28.260 align:middle line:90%
talk to anyone.

00:30:28.260 --> 00:30:30.690 align:middle line:84%
They are bound
only by God's will.

00:30:30.690 --> 00:30:33.060 align:middle line:90%
So so long as it's not a--

00:30:33.060 --> 00:30:36.180 align:middle line:84%
I can't imagine that any of us
would have the power to keep

00:30:36.180 --> 00:30:38.070 align:middle line:84%
an angel out even
if we wanted to,

00:30:38.070 --> 00:30:41.460 align:middle line:84%
but they, of course,
do not appear in hell.

00:30:41.460 --> 00:30:44.970 align:middle line:84%
The only time a being
appeared in hell

00:30:44.970 --> 00:30:46.840 align:middle line:84%
was Christ after
his crucifixion.

00:30:46.840 --> 00:30:49.620 align:middle line:84%
But otherwise, they don't
go-- that's not their realm.

00:30:49.620 --> 00:30:51.960 align:middle line:84%
That is another realm
they do not go into.

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:53.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does
Michael the archangel

00:30:53.940 --> 00:30:59.350 align:middle line:84%
appear when you ask for him
or does it appear on its own?

00:30:59.350 --> 00:31:01.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He will appear
completely on his own.

00:31:01.770 --> 00:31:07.550 align:middle line:84%
They are able to
act in their wills--

00:31:07.550 --> 00:31:10.370 align:middle line:84%
fulfilling God's will,
but they will often

00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:13.710 align:middle line:84%
appear when we do ask for them,
whether we can see them or not.

00:31:13.710 --> 00:31:16.010 align:middle line:84%
So I do believe that
each time every one of us

00:31:16.010 --> 00:31:20.712 align:middle line:84%
prays, say the archangel Michael
prayer, we are calling on him

00:31:20.712 --> 00:31:21.920 align:middle line:90%
and he is looking out for us.

00:31:21.920 --> 00:31:23.853 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell us about
sacred sites, Michael.

00:31:23.853 --> 00:31:24.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Absolutely.

00:31:24.770 --> 00:31:26.478 align:middle line:84%
One of the most
interesting sacred sites,

00:31:26.478 --> 00:31:28.190 align:middle line:84%
especially associated
with, say, Michael,

00:31:28.190 --> 00:31:30.320 align:middle line:84%
is, for me, Skellig
Michael, which

00:31:30.320 --> 00:31:33.530 align:middle line:84%
was set up by monks on
the west side of Ireland.

00:31:33.530 --> 00:31:36.560 align:middle line:84%
If anyone remembers the
latest "Star Wars" movies,

00:31:36.560 --> 00:31:39.080 align:middle line:84%
that's where Luke
Skywalker was hanging out,

00:31:39.080 --> 00:31:40.190 align:middle line:90%
at Skellig Michael.

00:31:40.190 --> 00:31:41.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:31:41.030 --> 00:31:42.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: For the
medieval person,

00:31:42.680 --> 00:31:44.390 align:middle line:90%
that was the edge of the world.

00:31:44.390 --> 00:31:47.070 align:middle line:84%
You could not go further
west if you wanted to.

00:31:47.070 --> 00:31:49.880 align:middle line:84%
So it was at the very
edge of civilization.

00:31:49.880 --> 00:31:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And it was a perfect
place for Irish monks

00:31:52.100 --> 00:31:54.710 align:middle line:84%
to set up to do
their translations,

00:31:54.710 --> 00:31:56.787 align:middle line:84%
but they had a
particular devotion

00:31:56.787 --> 00:31:58.370 align:middle line:84%
to the Archangel
Michael, who was said

00:31:58.370 --> 00:32:00.320 align:middle line:90%
to appear to the first monks.

00:32:00.320 --> 00:32:03.800 align:middle line:84%
And that is at the very tip
of the sword of Saint Michael,

00:32:03.800 --> 00:32:05.480 align:middle line:90%
running down to Jerusalem.

00:32:05.480 --> 00:32:07.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Our colleague,
Freddy Silva,

00:32:07.250 --> 00:32:10.820 align:middle line:84%
appeared on Gaia's "Open
Minds" about these sacred sites

00:32:10.820 --> 00:32:15.550 align:middle line:84%
that apparently are awakening
humans all over the place.

00:32:15.550 --> 00:32:16.350 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:32:16.350 --> 00:32:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>> This is really
about human awakening.

00:32:18.890 --> 00:32:22.610 align:middle line:84%
All of these sites are about
awakening our own consciousness

00:32:22.610 --> 00:32:23.900 align:middle line:90%
and coming to know ourselves.

00:32:23.900 --> 00:32:24.700 align:middle line:90%
Is that correct?

00:32:24.700 --> 00:32:25.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, absolutely.

00:32:25.640 --> 00:32:27.800 align:middle line:10%
If you go to any of the
temples around the world

00:32:27.800 --> 00:32:29.960 align:middle line:10%
and particularly
the ones in Egypt,

00:32:29.960 --> 00:32:32.902 align:middle line:10%
the ones in Southern India,
who are still very much intact,

00:32:32.902 --> 00:32:35.360 align:middle line:10%
they still have a lot of their
texts written on the walls--

00:32:35.360 --> 00:32:38.330 align:middle line:10%
and once we sat down to decipher
what the text is saying,

00:32:38.330 --> 00:32:40.940 align:middle line:10%
it's quite clear that all
of them are in agreement.

00:32:40.940 --> 00:32:42.990 align:middle line:84%
There's one in Temple
of Edfu, for example,

00:32:42.990 --> 00:32:45.620 align:middle line:84%
that talks about how the
temple is built to transform

00:32:45.620 --> 00:32:49.070 align:middle line:84%
the person into a god, into
a bright star, which is not

00:32:49.070 --> 00:32:52.130 align:middle line:84%
a bad reason to go there
in the first place.

00:32:52.130 --> 00:32:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And other temples talk about how
these are transmutation points

00:32:55.310 --> 00:32:58.520 align:middle line:84%
of the soul where heaven
connects with Earth, where

00:32:58.520 --> 00:33:00.710 align:middle line:84%
the temple is a kind
of living intermediary

00:33:00.710 --> 00:33:03.540 align:middle line:84%
between the physical human
and everything else that's

00:33:03.540 --> 00:33:04.340 align:middle line:90%
in the cosmos.

00:33:04.340 --> 00:33:07.580 align:middle line:84%
So in a way, it almost
reminds you that whenever

00:33:07.580 --> 00:33:08.480 align:middle line:90%
you lose the plot--

00:33:08.480 --> 00:33:11.630 align:middle line:84%
and we do this regularly
all the time these days--

00:33:11.630 --> 00:33:14.120 align:middle line:84%
the ancestors who
built these temples

00:33:14.120 --> 00:33:15.680 align:middle line:84%
left us the
instructions of where

00:33:15.680 --> 00:33:18.440 align:middle line:84%
to go, certain hot spots
on the face of the Earth,

00:33:18.440 --> 00:33:19.880 align:middle line:84%
where we can go
and basically tune

00:33:19.880 --> 00:33:21.630 align:middle line:84%
into the rest of the
universe and find out

00:33:21.630 --> 00:33:22.790 align:middle line:90%
how things really are.

00:33:22.790 --> 00:33:26.480 align:middle line:84%
Get to know ourselves, get to
know the purpose of our soul.

00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:30.567 align:middle line:84%
And by doing that in this kind
of quasi-shamanic environment,

00:33:30.567 --> 00:33:32.150 align:middle line:84%
then you are able
to more or less live

00:33:32.150 --> 00:33:34.880 align:middle line:84%
your life with a certain
degree of self-empowerment.

00:33:34.880 --> 00:33:38.360 align:middle line:84%
And when you have that degree
of self-awareness in your life,

00:33:38.360 --> 00:33:40.312 align:middle line:84%
no one or anything can
tell you what to do,

00:33:40.312 --> 00:33:42.020 align:middle line:84%
which is not a bad
way to live your life.

00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:43.190 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it's not.

00:33:43.190 --> 00:33:49.580 align:middle line:84%
And that has been dampened,
some can say, by intent.

00:33:49.580 --> 00:33:51.950 align:middle line:84%
It's not an accident
that these edifices

00:33:51.950 --> 00:33:55.580 align:middle line:84%
have been destroyed over
the last few thousand years,

00:33:55.580 --> 00:33:56.630 align:middle line:90%
in particular.

00:33:56.630 --> 00:33:59.150 align:middle line:84%
And there has been
a great detriment,

00:33:59.150 --> 00:34:02.330 align:middle line:84%
but the reality is, as
we're going to get into,

00:34:02.330 --> 00:34:04.490 align:middle line:84%
these places are
built on sacred spots

00:34:04.490 --> 00:34:07.340 align:middle line:84%
that even if the dwelling
should fall down,

00:34:07.340 --> 00:34:09.949 align:middle line:84%
if you knew where to go, they
have the same effect on us,

00:34:09.949 --> 00:34:10.749 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:34:10.749 --> 00:34:11.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:34:11.630 --> 00:34:14.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're all
harnessed with natural laws.

00:34:14.420 --> 00:34:17.659 align:middle line:84%
And today, we have the
mechanism to understand what

00:34:17.659 --> 00:34:19.400 align:middle line:84%
the natural laws
they were harnessing.

00:34:19.400 --> 00:34:20.200 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:34:20.200 --> 00:34:25.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Michael, do all
religions deal with angels?

00:34:25.330 --> 00:34:26.889 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: The
Abrahamic faiths do.

00:34:26.889 --> 00:34:28.330 align:middle line:84%
When you get into
other religions,

00:34:28.330 --> 00:34:31.780 align:middle line:84%
you'll have intermediaries,
messengers that look--

00:34:31.780 --> 00:34:34.330 align:middle line:84%
from my very layman
understanding,

00:34:34.330 --> 00:34:36.429 align:middle line:90%
sound like angels to me.

00:34:36.429 --> 00:34:38.320 align:middle line:90%
Hermes is a good example.

00:34:38.320 --> 00:34:41.679 align:middle line:84%
He's the God that talks to the
other gods on behalf of us.

00:34:41.679 --> 00:34:44.590 align:middle line:84%
It starts to sound very angelic
when you get down to it.

00:34:44.590 --> 00:34:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And of many places
where Saint Michael

00:34:48.100 --> 00:34:50.530 align:middle line:84%
had sacred sites
built to him, were

00:34:50.530 --> 00:34:53.230 align:middle line:90%
previously temples to Apollo.

00:34:53.230 --> 00:34:55.840 align:middle line:84%
So it's almost as if he
came through and revealed,

00:34:55.840 --> 00:34:59.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm the actual Apollo, but we're
still building on his temple.

00:34:59.650 --> 00:35:01.630 align:middle line:84%
It was a sacred site
before Christianity.

00:35:01.630 --> 00:35:03.430 align:middle line:84%
Long after Christianity,
would probably

00:35:03.430 --> 00:35:05.020 align:middle line:90%
continue to be a sacred site.

00:35:05.020 --> 00:35:09.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are these sites
dedicated to anything specific?

00:35:09.100 --> 00:35:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Usually,
an appearance

00:35:10.810 --> 00:35:15.910 align:middle line:84%
or an event that
happened, many pilgrims go

00:35:15.910 --> 00:35:17.858 align:middle line:84%
to Fatima or Lourdes
because that's

00:35:17.858 --> 00:35:20.025 align:middle line:84%
where the Virgin Mary and
other characters appeared.

00:35:20.025 --> 00:35:21.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Appeared, yeah.

00:35:21.920 --> 00:35:26.150 align:middle line:84%
And Lourdes is a fascinating
place all by itself, isn't it?

00:35:26.150 --> 00:35:27.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: People still--

00:35:27.230 --> 00:35:29.330 align:middle line:90%
I have a friend of mine--

00:35:29.330 --> 00:35:31.100 align:middle line:84%
I get goosebumps
when I think of him.

00:35:31.100 --> 00:35:33.350 align:middle line:84%
He was the father of
my friend, Danny--

00:35:33.350 --> 00:35:36.080 align:middle line:84%
went to Lourdes
after dealing with--

00:35:36.080 --> 00:35:38.925 align:middle line:84%
trying to remember-- I
believe it was colon cancer.

00:35:38.925 --> 00:35:39.725 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, God.

00:35:39.725 --> 00:35:41.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: But healed.

00:35:41.090 --> 00:35:42.132 align:middle line:90%
He's still alive with us.

00:35:42.132 --> 00:35:42.932 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Healed?

00:35:42.932 --> 00:35:44.300 align:middle line:90%
Did he jump in the water?

00:35:44.300 --> 00:35:46.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: He did
bathe in the water

00:35:46.250 --> 00:35:48.920 align:middle line:84%
and he also attended mass
and did some fasting.

00:35:48.920 --> 00:35:51.425 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't sure anything would
happen, but weeks later,

00:35:51.425 --> 00:35:53.300 align:middle line:84%
the doctor is like
everything's in remission.

00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:55.230 align:middle line:90%
You're fine.

00:35:55.230 --> 00:35:58.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you feel about
people who do not believe?

00:35:58.340 --> 00:35:59.870 align:middle line:90%
They don't believe in angels.

00:35:59.870 --> 00:36:03.342 align:middle line:84%
They don't believe
in a higher power.

00:36:03.342 --> 00:36:04.300 align:middle line:90%
It's their prerogative.

00:36:04.300 --> 00:36:04.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: Yeah.

00:36:04.840 --> 00:36:05.170 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:36:05.170 --> 00:36:06.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But what do you think?

00:36:06.010 --> 00:36:07.930 align:middle line:84%
What are they missing
in their life?

00:36:07.930 --> 00:36:10.180 align:middle line:10%
>>LICHENS: Oh, I think
some skepticism is always

00:36:10.180 --> 00:36:14.010 align:middle line:10%
a little healthy, but I
think with a lot of people,

00:36:14.010 --> 00:36:17.100 align:middle line:10%
it's because it's hard to
get outside of the hustle

00:36:17.100 --> 00:36:18.480 align:middle line:10%
and bustle of every day.

00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:21.370 align:middle line:84%
We have-- our lives
are determined

00:36:21.370 --> 00:36:23.710 align:middle line:84%
by the clock and the people
who are running the clock,

00:36:23.710 --> 00:36:26.500 align:middle line:84%
so it's easy to get
caught up in the imminent

00:36:26.500 --> 00:36:28.360 align:middle line:84%
without thinking
about the mystical

00:36:28.360 --> 00:36:30.640 align:middle line:90%
because we live and die by it.

00:36:30.640 --> 00:36:33.700 align:middle line:84%
And what I often want
to stress to people

00:36:33.700 --> 00:36:37.420 align:middle line:84%
is I don't believe in
angels or the greater powers

00:36:37.420 --> 00:36:39.380 align:middle line:90%
because I want a child's story.

00:36:39.380 --> 00:36:40.780 align:middle line:10%
It's because I want to know--

00:36:40.780 --> 00:36:43.590 align:middle line:10%
I know in my deepest heart
that there is something bigger

00:36:43.590 --> 00:36:44.390 align:middle line:10%
than us.

00:36:44.390 --> 00:36:45.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's
something there.

00:36:45.320 --> 00:36:46.403 align:middle line:90%
There's no doubt about it.

00:36:46.403 --> 00:36:48.340 align:middle line:84%
Do you find the
angels appear more

00:36:48.340 --> 00:36:52.140 align:middle line:84%
during years and
moments of strife?

00:36:52.140 --> 00:36:54.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Based off the history
and especially the mysticism,

00:36:54.840 --> 00:36:57.030 align:middle line:84%
like the hundreds
of encounters people

00:36:57.030 --> 00:37:00.270 align:middle line:84%
had with angels and
also Saints and ghosts

00:37:00.270 --> 00:37:02.760 align:middle line:90%
during World War I is insane.

00:37:02.760 --> 00:37:04.710 align:middle line:10%
The Guardian ran a
piece about how many

00:37:04.710 --> 00:37:06.750 align:middle line:10%
people encountered
ghosts or angels

00:37:06.750 --> 00:37:10.080 align:middle line:10%
during the Western Front.

00:37:10.080 --> 00:37:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And you think yeah,
that's probably

00:37:11.760 --> 00:37:15.420 align:middle line:84%
the time we need them the
most, when we can't rely just

00:37:15.420 --> 00:37:16.650 align:middle line:90%
on our own understanding.

00:37:16.650 --> 00:37:18.060 align:middle line:90%
We really need them.

00:37:18.060 --> 00:37:20.430 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's when
they deliver greatly.

00:37:20.430 --> 00:37:23.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What does prayer
mean to you, Michael?

00:37:23.190 --> 00:37:26.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Prayer to me is
communication but more than

00:37:26.340 --> 00:37:29.700 align:middle line:84%
that, it's opening yourself
up to God in his will,

00:37:29.700 --> 00:37:33.087 align:middle line:84%
to say to him whatever it is
you need of me, whatever it is

00:37:33.087 --> 00:37:35.670 align:middle line:84%
you want of me, I want to do it
even if I can't see the bigger

00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:38.380 align:middle line:84%
picture because you can
see the bigger picture.

00:37:38.380 --> 00:37:40.780 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
want to be part of.

00:37:40.780 --> 00:37:44.220 align:middle line:84%
And so when we pray to
God or even ask his angels

00:37:44.220 --> 00:37:46.590 align:middle line:84%
for assistance, we're
opening ourselves

00:37:46.590 --> 00:37:48.690 align:middle line:90%
up to a lot more possibility.

00:37:48.690 --> 00:37:51.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you ever
had an angelic experience?

00:37:51.270 --> 00:37:52.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: I have not.

00:37:52.680 --> 00:37:54.210 align:middle line:90%
My grandmother did.

00:37:54.210 --> 00:37:56.370 align:middle line:84%
My grandmother
swears up and down

00:37:56.370 --> 00:37:58.980 align:middle line:84%
that she was saved from
walking into oncoming traffic

00:37:58.980 --> 00:38:00.507 align:middle line:84%
by an angel because
she thought--

00:38:00.507 --> 00:38:01.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Pushed her aside.

00:38:01.590 --> 00:38:03.673 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Grabbed her
shoulders, pulled her back,

00:38:03.673 --> 00:38:05.565 align:middle line:90%
and there was no one around her.

00:38:05.565 --> 00:38:06.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But she felt that.

00:38:06.690 --> 00:38:07.830 align:middle line:90%
She felt that.

00:38:07.830 --> 00:38:09.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: She
looked behind herself

00:38:09.420 --> 00:38:11.590 align:middle line:84%
to say thank you, I
really appreciate it,

00:38:11.590 --> 00:38:13.620 align:middle line:84%
and there was no
one there to thank.

00:38:13.620 --> 00:38:15.540 align:middle line:84%
So she had to
instead say thank you

00:38:15.540 --> 00:38:17.940 align:middle line:84%
in prayer, which was one
of the things she taught

00:38:17.940 --> 00:38:20.460 align:middle line:84%
me, was always be thankful
for your guardian angel

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:22.920 align:middle line:84%
because you don't know how
many times they saved you.

00:38:22.920 --> 00:38:26.585 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are the angels
working on their own?

00:38:26.585 --> 00:38:27.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: They can--

00:38:27.460 --> 00:38:28.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or is it
all through God?

00:38:28.630 --> 00:38:29.963 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: It's all through God.

00:38:29.963 --> 00:38:31.540 align:middle line:84%
They do have some
free will, but they

00:38:31.540 --> 00:38:36.430 align:middle line:84%
are working through God's
will and will generally not go

00:38:36.430 --> 00:38:37.360 align:middle line:90%
against his will.

00:38:37.360 --> 00:38:39.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I keep thinking
of that Nicolas Cage

00:38:39.250 --> 00:38:40.842 align:middle line:90%
movie, "City of Angels."

00:38:40.842 --> 00:38:42.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: I love that movie.

00:38:42.050 --> 00:38:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And that depicts him as a
human being but an angel.

00:38:47.020 --> 00:38:49.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they really
out there like that?

00:38:49.750 --> 00:38:52.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: That's an
interesting depiction of angels.

00:38:52.720 --> 00:38:55.450 align:middle line:84%
What I liked about it was
that the angels had no more

00:38:55.450 --> 00:38:57.010 align:middle line:84%
understanding of
God than we did,

00:38:57.010 --> 00:39:00.430 align:middle line:84%
but they were still
fulfilling God's will.

00:39:00.430 --> 00:39:02.080 align:middle line:90%
I don't have any--

00:39:02.080 --> 00:39:03.970 align:middle line:84%
it's a great artistic
device, but I

00:39:03.970 --> 00:39:05.980 align:middle line:84%
don't know of any
mystic who has ever

00:39:05.980 --> 00:39:09.040 align:middle line:84%
said that angels are just
wandering the library,

00:39:09.040 --> 00:39:10.600 align:middle line:90%
asking the same questions.

00:39:10.600 --> 00:39:14.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We heard stories
about Saint Michael

00:39:14.230 --> 00:39:16.870 align:middle line:90%
getting involved in events.

00:39:16.870 --> 00:39:20.320 align:middle line:90%
How often is that happening?

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:23.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: It's hard to
tell because many times, I--

00:39:23.460 --> 00:39:26.880 align:middle line:84%
many times, angels can
appear to us completely

00:39:26.880 --> 00:39:29.100 align:middle line:90%
and we're completely unaware.

00:39:29.100 --> 00:39:30.875 align:middle line:84%
Saints, going back
to the Old Testament,

00:39:30.875 --> 00:39:33.000 align:middle line:84%
have talked about they had
no idea they encountered

00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:35.800 align:middle line:90%
an angel until much later.

00:39:35.800 --> 00:39:36.930 align:middle line:90%
So who knows how often?

00:39:36.930 --> 00:39:38.388 align:middle line:84%
There's a good
chance that somebody

00:39:38.388 --> 00:39:41.370 align:middle line:84%
who gave you helpful advice
or lifted your spirits one day

00:39:41.370 --> 00:39:43.620 align:middle line:90%
was just an angel in disguise.

00:39:43.620 --> 00:39:45.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they have
messages for us, Michael?

00:39:45.660 --> 00:39:46.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: They do.

00:39:46.560 --> 00:39:47.910 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What might they be?

00:39:47.910 --> 00:39:49.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: The
messages are often--

00:39:49.920 --> 00:39:51.690 align:middle line:84%
depending on the
person and place,

00:39:51.690 --> 00:39:55.500 align:middle line:84%
they are often a similar
message which is, of course,

00:39:55.500 --> 00:40:00.120 align:middle line:84%
repent, flee from your sins,
but also return to God.

00:40:00.120 --> 00:40:03.300 align:middle line:84%
They're asking you to come
back because many of us

00:40:03.300 --> 00:40:06.870 align:middle line:84%
need that wake-up call
often in our lives.

00:40:06.870 --> 00:40:11.430 align:middle line:84%
Their messages are also of
hope that this life, whatever

00:40:11.430 --> 00:40:15.960 align:middle line:84%
travails we're having, whatever
world wars, diseases, famines,

00:40:15.960 --> 00:40:17.730 align:middle line:90%
there is still hope for us.

00:40:17.730 --> 00:40:21.300 align:middle line:84%
And again, their very existence
shows we're not left alone.

00:40:21.300 --> 00:40:22.660 align:middle line:90%
We're not an accident.

00:40:22.660 --> 00:40:24.000 align:middle line:90%
We are here for a purpose.

00:40:24.000 --> 00:40:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you
channel an angel?

00:40:27.150 --> 00:40:28.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: I don't know.

00:40:28.200 --> 00:40:29.160 align:middle line:90%
Many people have tried.

00:40:29.160 --> 00:40:30.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't know of any
successful ones.

00:40:30.660 --> 00:40:32.280 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be
too close-minded,

00:40:32.280 --> 00:40:34.680 align:middle line:84%
but angels will often
talk through people,

00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:36.120 align:middle line:90%
deliver messages for others.

00:40:36.120 --> 00:40:38.910 align:middle line:84%
Padre Pio would often tell
people what their guardian

00:40:38.910 --> 00:40:41.100 align:middle line:84%
angel was trying to
tell them, but they just

00:40:41.100 --> 00:40:43.200 align:middle line:84%
couldn't hear, for
whatever reason.

00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:46.740 align:middle line:84%
And he received those
messages frequently.

00:40:46.740 --> 00:40:49.070 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who is Theo?

00:40:49.070 --> 00:40:53.302 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: Theo is the
name of God in Latin.

00:40:53.302 --> 00:40:56.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And there's also a
collectiveness of archangels

00:40:56.280 --> 00:41:00.000 align:middle line:90%
under that umbrella.

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:01.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: And they are--

00:41:01.920 --> 00:41:04.020 align:middle line:84%
that is the higher angels,
what we were talking

00:41:04.020 --> 00:41:05.430 align:middle line:90%
about in a previous video.

00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:08.730 align:middle line:84%
Those are the Thrones, the
Watchers, you might call them,

00:41:08.730 --> 00:41:10.410 align:middle line:90%
who are overseeing--

00:41:10.410 --> 00:41:12.390 align:middle line:90%
they are closest to God.

00:41:12.390 --> 00:41:15.240 align:middle line:84%
They literally surround
him at all times,

00:41:15.240 --> 00:41:17.760 align:middle line:84%
so they know God
better than any of us.

00:41:17.760 --> 00:41:20.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sheila
Gillette channels Theo.

00:41:20.980 --> 00:41:21.780 align:middle line:90%
