>>NOORY: What do you
think of Sheila Gillette?

00:43:31.080 --> 00:43:33.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: That's fascinating.

00:43:33.870 --> 00:43:36.543 align:middle line:84%
I knew of several Renaissance
and medieval people

00:43:36.543 --> 00:43:37.710 align:middle line:90%
who tried to channel angels.

00:43:37.710 --> 00:43:39.840 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know it was still
happening in modern times.

00:43:39.840 --> 00:43:40.680 align:middle line:90%
It's fascinating.

00:43:40.680 --> 00:43:42.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You sound like
you might have the ability

00:43:42.480 --> 00:43:43.280 align:middle line:90%
to do it yourself.

00:43:43.280 --> 00:43:45.893 align:middle line:90%


00:43:45.893 --> 00:43:47.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: I don't think so.

00:43:47.060 --> 00:43:50.060 align:middle line:84%
My family has many
weird abilities when

00:43:50.060 --> 00:43:51.920 align:middle line:90%
observing and seeing ghosts.

00:43:51.920 --> 00:43:54.580 align:middle line:84%
I have not seen an angel,
though, or encountered one.

00:43:54.580 --> 00:43:55.580 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do you want to?

00:43:55.580 --> 00:43:57.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: I do, but--

00:43:57.110 --> 00:43:58.190 align:middle line:90%
I do and I don't.

00:43:58.190 --> 00:43:59.810 align:middle line:84%
I do, on the one
hand, because I would

00:43:59.810 --> 00:44:04.340 align:middle line:84%
love to have that
affirmation and just

00:44:04.340 --> 00:44:06.190 align:middle line:90%
that proof for my own eyes.

00:44:06.190 --> 00:44:08.690 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, I don't want
to see an angel because they

00:44:08.690 --> 00:44:10.640 align:middle line:90%
often have to give you work.

00:44:10.640 --> 00:44:12.392 align:middle line:84%
They often are
assigning you something.

00:44:12.392 --> 00:44:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And all I could think is if
an angel is coming to me,

00:44:14.600 --> 00:44:17.040 align:middle line:90%
they're really desperate.

00:44:17.040 --> 00:44:19.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'll tell you
an interesting story.

00:44:19.530 --> 00:44:23.040 align:middle line:84%
My mother was raised
in the Boston area.

00:44:23.040 --> 00:44:28.080 align:middle line:84%
And her parents owned a
series of apartment complexes

00:44:28.080 --> 00:44:31.830 align:middle line:84%
over a furniture
store that they owned.

00:44:31.830 --> 00:44:37.560 align:middle line:84%
And they had four apartments all
adjoining that they lived in.

00:44:37.560 --> 00:44:39.750 align:middle line:90%
And we'd go there every summer.

00:44:39.750 --> 00:44:45.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, one night, we got woken
up by a fireman with a mask

00:44:45.500 --> 00:44:51.170 align:middle line:84%
on at like 3:00 in the morning,
smoke engulfing the apartment.

00:44:51.170 --> 00:44:54.540 align:middle line:84%
And he woke everybody
up and got us all out.

00:44:54.540 --> 00:44:57.290 align:middle line:84%
There was a picture of me in
the "Fitchburg Massachusetts

00:44:57.290 --> 00:45:01.040 align:middle line:84%
Gazette" running across the
street in my little pajamas.

00:45:01.040 --> 00:45:03.830 align:middle line:84%
I must have been seven
or eight years old.

00:45:03.830 --> 00:45:07.550 align:middle line:84%
But this angel, whatever it
might have been, saved us.

00:45:07.550 --> 00:45:11.360 align:middle line:84%
Well, my father went up
to the fire department

00:45:11.360 --> 00:45:16.500 align:middle line:84%
after the fact because smoke
was billowing outside, and said,

00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:19.820 align:middle line:84%
we want to thank that
fireman who was in there.

00:45:19.820 --> 00:45:24.230 align:middle line:84%
And they said we haven't
gotten in there yet.

00:45:24.230 --> 00:45:25.700 align:middle line:90%
Who was he?

00:45:25.700 --> 00:45:28.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: That's intense.

00:45:28.580 --> 00:45:31.250 align:middle line:10%
I can't believe I'm returning
to his name for this story,

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:33.930 align:middle line:10%
but Saint Michael is the
patron of firefighters.

00:45:33.930 --> 00:45:34.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:45:34.730 --> 00:45:35.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: He is.

00:45:35.530 --> 00:45:38.180 align:middle line:84%
A lot of firefighters,
especially in the Boston area,

00:45:38.180 --> 00:45:40.100 align:middle line:84%
will wear a Saint Michael's
medallion on them.

00:45:40.100 --> 00:45:41.310 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:45:41.310 --> 00:45:42.362 align:middle line:90%
>>LICHENS: So he's--

00:45:42.362 --> 00:45:44.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'm convinced it
was an angel that saved us.

00:45:44.570 --> 00:45:45.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LICHENS: I am
too if I'm honest.

00:45:45.800 --> 00:45:47.967 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because they said
they never went up there.

00:45:47.967 --> 00:45:50.550 align:middle line:84%
They hadn't been up
there at that point.

00:45:50.550 --> 00:45:52.670 align:middle line:10%
>>LICHENS: So an
angel was looking out

00:45:52.670 --> 00:45:54.950 align:middle line:10%
for you and your
family, and they did it

00:45:54.950 --> 00:45:57.650 align:middle line:10%
as they often do, in disguise,
because they don't necessarily

00:45:57.650 --> 00:46:01.030 align:middle line:10%
need our gratitude,
but that's insane.

